  , issueCommentBody =
      "Underscore has considered and refused to implement concatMap. They instead have a syntax I'm not too crazy about:\r\n\r\n    _.chain(Customers)\r\n      .map((customer) -> customer.orders()).flatten()\r\n      .map((order) -> order.lineItems()).flatten()\r\n      .value()\r\n\r\nIn rethinkdb this would be:\r\n\r\n    Customers.concatMap(r.row[\"orders\"] + r.row[\"lineItems\"])\r\n\r\nI can't find a mongo syntax for concatMap maybe I'm just missing it.\r\n\r\nEither way we need concat map because other crucial features desugar to it but we don't need to expose it to users if the name is too daunting."
